    en: "New York's Volunteer Firefighters' Benefit Law (VFBL) provides workers-compensation-like benefits to the approximately 70,000 volunteer firefighters in New York who are injured or killed while performing duties. Benefits include medical care, lost-wage replacement, disability pensions, and death benefits to surviving spouses and dependents. Benefits are paid from the sponsoring fire district or municipality's insurance (typically through the NYS Insurance Fund). Claims are filed with the district and processed through the Workers' Compensation Board. VFBL is independent of federal or state workers' compensation but uses similar procedures. A parallel Volunteer Ambulance Workers' Benefit Law (VAWBL) covers volunteer EMS workers under similar rules."
